         <div type="translation">
            <p>[To the Divine] Spirits. To [- -] Rufus. [- -] Rufus (made this?) for (his) patron, [w]ell-deserving, [who] lived for [X] years, [X months? (and) X d]ay[s].</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 2: The abbreviation of the praenomen and all but the end of the gentilicium of the dedicatee are missing.</p>
            <p>Line 3: The abbreviation of the praenomen and all but the final "s" of the gentilicium of the dedicator are missing.</p>
            <p>Line 5: The numeral indicating the number of years lived is incomplete. It is at least twenty.</p>
            <p>Line 6: The final line seems to include part of an ablative ending indicating the number of days lived; whether or not it was preceded by a number of months is uncertain.</p>
         </div>
